gh plugin pipeline)\ninterface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;        // output path -> rendered content\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;        // output path -> binary data\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;         // shared plugin data store\n}\n\n// Plugin hooks\ninterface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\n// Plugin interface\ninterface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];             // plugin names this depends on\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\n// Template interface\ninterface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. BUILD ENGINE (src/core/engine.ts)\n\nThe `BuildEngine` class:\n\n- **Constructor**: Takes `SiteConfig`\n- **registerPlugin(plugin)**: Adds plugin to execution queue\n- **registerTemplate(template)**: Registers named templates\n- **resolvePluginOrder()**: Topological sort to resolve dependencies\n  - Detects circular dependencies and missing dependencies\n  - Returns plugins in correct execution order\n- **async build(files)**: Main build process:\n  1. Create BuildContext with input files\n  2. Call `beforeBuild` hooks on all plugins (in dependency order)\n  3. Call `transformContent` hooks on all files for each plugin\n  4. Render files using templates (or raw content if no template)\n  5. Call `afterBuild` hooks on all plugins\n  6. Return completed BuildContext\n- **getPlugins()**: Returns plugin list copy\n- **getTemplates()**: Returns templates map copy\n\n**Key Feature**: The `ctx.data` Map is a shared state store that plugins can use to pass data downstream.\n\n---\n\n### 4. CORE TESTS (tests/core.test.ts - 15 tests)\n\nAll 15 existing tests MUST continue to pass:\n\n1. **Plugin registration** - Engine registers and retrieves plugins\n2. **Template registration** - Engine registers and retrieves templates\n3. **Default template rendering** - Renders with `<!DOCTYPE html>`, title, content\n4. **List template rendering** - Renders with `<div class=\"list\">`\n5. **Raw content output** - Falls back to raw content when no template\n6. **beforeBuild hook** - Plugin hook is called\n7. **transformContent hook** - Files are transformed via plugin hook\n8. **afterBuild hook** - Plugin hook is called\n9. **Plugin execution order** - Dependencies resolved correctly\n10. **Circular dependency detection** - Throws error on circular deps\n11. **Missing dependency detection** - Throws error on missing deps\n12. **Multiple plugins transformContent** - Plugins applied in dependency order\n13. **Shared data store** - ctx.data persists across plugins\n14. **Metadata preservation** - File metadata, dates, tags retained through build\n15. **Empty file list** - Handles empty input gracefully\n\n---\n\n### 5. PLUGIN TEST FILES - COMPLETE TEST SPECIFICATIONS\n\n#### **WAVE 1 PLUGINS (No Dependencies)**\n\n---\n\n##### **markdown-ext Plugin** (tests/plugins/markdown-ext.test.ts - 8 tests)\n\n**Factory Function**: `createMarkdownExtPlugin()`\n\n**Plugin Metadata**:\n- name: `'markdown-ext'`\n- version: `'1.0.0'`\n- dependencies: `[]`\n\n**Hooks**: `transformContent` only\n\n**Tests** (8 total):\n\n1. **converts basic markdown to HTML** - `'# Hello\\n\\nThis is a **bold** paragraph.'` → Contains `<h1>Hello</h1>` and `<strong>bold</strong>`\n\n2. **handles footnotes with [^1] syntax** - `'Some text[^1] here.\\n\\n[^1]: This is the footnote.'` → Contains `<sup><a href=\"#fn-1\">1</a></sup>`\n\n3. **renders footnote section at bottom** - `'Text[^1] and more[^2].\\n\\n[^1]: First note.\\n[^2]: Second note.'` → Contains:\n   - `<section class=\"footnotes\">`\n   - `<li id=\"fn-1\">First note.</li>`\n   - `<li id=\"fn-2\">Second note.</li>`\n\n4. **converts :::note container to admonition div** - `':::note\\nThis is a note.\\n:::'` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-note\">This is a note.</div>`\n\n5. **converts :::warning container** - `':::warning\\nBe careful!\\n:::'` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-warning\">Be careful!</div>`\n\n6. **converts :::tip container** - `':::tip\\nHelpful hint.\\n:::'` → `<div class=\"admonition admonition-tip\">Helpful hint.</div>`\n\n7. **preserves existing HTML** - Already-HTML content passes through unchanged\n\n8. **handles empty content** - Empty string returns defined content (not error)\n\n**Dependencies**: Uses `marked` package for markdown parsing\n\n---\n\n##### **asset-pipeline Plugin** (tests/plugins/asset-pipeline.test.ts - 9 tests)\n\n**Factory Function**: `createAssetPipelinePlugin()`\n\n**Plugin Metadata**:\n- name: `'asset-pipeline'`\n- version: `'1.0.0'`\n- dependencies: `[]`\n\n**Hooks**: `transformContent`\n\n**Tests** (9 total):\n\n1. **rewrites relative image URLs** - `<img src=\"./image.png\">` → `<img src=\"/assets/image.png\">`\n\n2. **rewrites relative link URLs** - `<a href=\"./doc.pdf\">` → `<a href=\"/assets/doc.pdf\">`\n\n3. **leaves absolute URLs unchanged** - `https://cdn.example.com/image.png` stays as-is\n\n4. **generates asset manifest in ctx.data** - Creates `ctx.data.set('asset-manifest', { assets: string[] })`\n\n5. **handles files with no asset references** - No changes to content without relative assets\n\n6. **handles multiple assets in one file** - All assets collected: `['a.png', 'b.jpg', 'c.pdf']`\n\n7. **asset manifest includes all discovered assets** - Accumulates across multiple transformContent calls\n\n8. **does not double-process rewritten URLs** - `src=\"/assets/image.png\"` doesn't get re-processed\n\n9. **data structure**: `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')` returns `{ assets: string[] }`\n\n---\n\n##### **syntax-highlight Plugin** (tests/plugins/syntax-highlight.test.ts - 8 tests)\n\n**Factory Function**: `createSyntaxHighlightPlugin()`\n\n**Plugin Metadata**:\n- name: `'syntax-highlight'`\n- version: `'1.0.0'`\n- dependencies: `[]`\n\n**Hooks**: `transformContent`\n\n**Tests** (8 total):\n\n1. **adds language class to code blocks** - `<code class=\"language-javascript\">` → `class=\"language-javascript highlighted\"`\n\n2. **adds data-language attribute to pre tags** - `<pre><code class=\"language-python\">` → `<pre data-language=\"python\"><code class=\"language-python highlighted\">`\n\n3. **handles multiple code blocks** - Processes all blocks in one file with their respective languages\n\n4. **handles code block with no language** - `<pre><code>plain code</code></pre>` → unchanged (no highlighted class)\n\n5. **adds highlighted class to processed blocks** - `<code class=\"language-rust\">` → `class=\"language-rust highlighted\"`\n\n6. **preserves code block content** - Original code text preserved in output\n\n7. **handles empty code blocks** - `<code class=\"language-js\"></code>` gets `highlighted` class and `data-language=\"js\"`\n\n8. **does not modify inline code** - `<code>` (not in `<pre>`) stays unchanged, no `highlighted` class\n\n**Behavior**: Targets `<pre><code class=\"language-*\">` patterns only, not inline code\n\n---\n\n#### **WAVE 2 PLUGINS (Depend on Wave 1)**\n\n---\n\n##### **taxonomy Plugin** (tests/plugins/taxonomy.test.ts - 10 tests)\n\n**Factory Function**: `createTaxonomyPlugin()`\n\n**Plugin Metadata**:\n- name: `'taxonomy'`\n- version: `'1.0.0'`\n- dependencies: `[]`\n\n**Hooks**: `beforeBuild`, `afterBuild`\n\n**Tests** (10 total):\n\n1. **builds tag index from file tags** - Files with tags → `ctx.data.set('taxonomy-tags', Map<string, ContentFile[]>)` mapping each tag to files\n\n2. **generates tag listing pages in ctx.output** - `ctx.output.set('tags/javascript.html', content)` for each tag\n\n3. **handles files with no tags** - Files without tags field don't create tag entries\n\n4. **handles files with multiple tags** - Single file with `['js', 'node', 'web']` creates 3 tag entries\n\n5. **tag pages list all files with that tag** - Multiple files with same tag listed together on tag page\n\n6. **stores tag map in ctx.data** - `ctx.data.has('taxonomy-tags')` → true\n\n7. **handles empty file list** - Zero files → empty tag map created\n\n8. **tags are case-normalized to lowercase**:\n   - Input: `['JavaScript', 'JAVASCRIPT']`\n   - Both map to lowercase `'javascript'`\n   - `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags').has('javascript')` → true (2 files)\n   - NOT stored as `'JavaScript'` or `'JAVASCRIPT'`\n\n9. **output structure**: `ctx.output.get('tags/{tag}.html')` contains HTML listing files with that tag\n\n10. **data structure**: `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` is `Map<string, ContentFile[]>`\n\n**Hook Behavior**:\n- `beforeBuild`: Build the tag map from ctx.files\n- `afterBuild`: Generate tag page HTML files to ctx.output\n\n---\n\n##### **rss-feed Plugin** (tests/plugins/rss-feed.test.ts - 8 tests)\n\n**Factory Function**: `createRssFeedPlugin()`\n\n**Plugin Metadata**:\n- name: `'rss-feed'`\n- version: `'1.0.0'`\n- dependencies: `['markdown-ext', 'taxonomy']`\n\n**Hooks**: `afterBuild`\n\n**Tests** (8 total):\n\n1. **generates valid RSS 2.0 XML** - Output contains:\n   ```xml\n   <?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n   <rss version=\"2.0\">\n   <channel>\n   <item>...</item>\n   </rss>\n   ```\n\n2. **feed items contain HTML content not raw markdown** - Content wrapped in `<![CDATA[<p>This is <strong>HTML</strong> content</p>]]>`\n\n3. **feed items include category tags from taxonomy** - Reads `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` and adds `<category>tag-name</category>` for each tag of a file\n\n4. **feed includes channel title from config** - `<title>{config.title}</title>`\n\n5. **feed items sorted by date newest first** - Items appear in reverse chronological order (2024-06-15 before 2024-01-01)\n\n6. **handles files without dates** - Files without `date` field included; pubDate omitted or handled gracefully\n\n7. **feed link uses baseUrl from config**:\n   - Channel link: `<link>{config.baseUrl}</link>`\n   - Item links: `<link>{config.baseUrl}/{slug}.html</link>`\n\n8. **output structure**: `ctx.output.set('feed.xml', rss_content)`\n\n---\n\n#### **WAVE 3 PLUGINS (Depend on Wave 2)**\n\n---\n\n##### **search-index Plugin** (tests/plugins/search-index.test.ts - 7 tests)\n\n**Factory Function**: `createSearchIndexPlugin()`\n\n**Plugin Metadata**:\n- name: `'search-index'`\n- version: `'1.0.0'`\n- dependencies: `['markdown-ext', 'syntax-highlight']`\n\n**Hooks**: `afterBuild`\n\n**Tests** (7 total):\n\n1. **generates search-index.json in ctx.output** - `ctx.output.has('search-index.json')` → true\n\n2. **index entries have title, slug, and plain text content**:\n   ```json\n   [\n     {\n       \"slug\": \"my-post\",\n       \"title\": \"My Post\",\n       \"content\": \"Some text here\"\n     }\n   ]\n   ```\n\n3. **HTML tags stripped from indexed content** - `<h1>Title</h1><p>text</p>` → `Title text` (no `<`, `>` characters)\n\n4. **code blocks included in searchable text** - `<code>const x = 1;</code>` text indexed\n\n5. **handles empty file list** - `[]` in output\n\n6. **search index is valid JSON** - Parses without error, is array\n\n7. **index entries include tags if present** - `tags: ['js', 'web']` included in index entry\n\n**Output Format**: JSON array, each object has `slug`, `title`, `content`, and optionally `tags`\n\n---\n\n##### **sitemap Plugin** (tests/plugins/sitemap.test.ts - 8 tests)\n\n**Factory Function**: `createSitemapPlugin()`\n\n**Plugin Metadata**:\n- name: `'sitemap'`\n- version: `'1.0.0'`\n- dependencies: `['taxonomy', 'rss-feed']`\n\n**Hooks**: `afterBuild`\n\n**Tests** (8 total):\n\n1. **generates sitemap.xml in ctx.output** - `ctx.output.has('sitemap.xml')` → true\n\n2. **includes all content page URLs** - All `.html` files from `ctx.output` → `https://example.com/post-1.html`, etc.\n\n3. **includes taxonomy tag page URLs** - Tag pages from `ctx.data.get('taxonomy-tags')` → `https://example.com/tags/javascript.html`\n\n4. **includes feed.xml URL** - `https://example.com/feed.xml` (if present in output)\n\n5. **URLs use baseUrl from config** - All URLs prefixed with `config.baseUrl`\n\n6. **sitemap is valid XML structure**:\n   ```xml\n   <?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n   <urlset>\n     <url>\n       <loc>...</loc>\n     </url>\n   </urlset>\n   ```\n\n7. **handles site with no tag pages** - Works with just content pages\n\n8. **output structure**: `ctx.output.set('sitemap.xml', xml_content)`\n\n---\n\n##### **dev-server Plugin** (tests/plugins/dev-server.test.ts - 7 tests)\n\n**Factory Function**: `createDevServerPlugin()`\n\n**Plugin Metadata**:\n- name: `'dev-server'`\n- version: `'1.0.0'`\n- dependencies: `['asset-pipeline', 'search-index']`\n\n**Hooks**: `afterBuild`\n\n**Interface** (from test):\n```typescript\ninterface DevServerConfig {\n  port: number;\n  routes: Array<{ path: string; handler: string }>;\n  assetPaths: string[];\n  searchIndexPath: string;\n}\n```\n\n**Tests** (7 total):\n\n1. **stores dev-server-config in ctx.data** - `ctx.data.has('dev-server-config')` → true\n\n2. **config includes port setting** - `config.port` is a number\n\n3. **config includes asset routes from asset-pipeline**:\n   - Reads `ctx.data.get('asset-manifest')`\n   - Creates routes with `handler: 'asset'`\n   - `assetPaths` contains all asset filenames\n\n4. **config includes search index path** - `searchIndexPath: '/search-index.json'` (if present in output)\n\n5. **config includes content routes**:\n   - All `.html` files from `ctx.output` become routes\n   - `handler: 'static'` for content routes\n\n6. **default port is 3000** - `config.port === 3000`\n\n7. **handles missing asset-pipeline data gracefully** - Works if `asset-manifest` not in ctx.data; `assetPaths: []`\n\n**Output Structure**: `ctx.data.set('dev-server-config', DevServerConfig)`\n\n---\n\n### 6. PACKAGE.JSON\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-ssg-toolkit\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"SSG Toolkit benchmark - static site generator with DAG plugin system\",\n  \"main\": \"dist/core/index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.57.1\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.9\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/marked\": \"^5.0.2\",\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"marked\": \"^17.0.2\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Points**:\n- ES Modules only (`\"type\": \"module\"`)\n- TypeScript strict mode\n- Using `marked` for markdown parsing\n- Express included (for dev-server plugin)\n- Test runner: `vitest`\n\n---\n\n### 7. TSCONFIG.JSON\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Configuration**:\n- Strict mode enabled\n- Target ES2022\n- CommonJS interop enabled\n- Declaration files generated\n\n---\n\n### 8. EXISTING PLUGINS IN src/plugins/\n\n**Status**: Directory is EMPTY (only `.gitkeep`)\n\n**Required**: Must create 8 plugin files:\n1. `markdown-ext.ts`\n2. `asset-pipeline.ts`\n3. `syntax-highlight.ts`\n4. `taxonomy.ts`\n5. `rss-feed.ts`\n6. `search-index.ts`\n7. `sitemap.ts`\n8. `dev-server.ts`\n\nEach must export a factory function: `createXxxPlugin()` returning a `Plugin` object.\n\n---\n\n### 9. VITEST CONFIG\n\n```typescript\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    globals: true,\n    testTimeout: 10000,\n  },\n});\n```\n\n**Settings**:\n- Global test functions enabled\n- 10-s